<p>The <a href="https://archive.org/details/twitter_cikm_2010">dataset</a> paints a fascinating picture of the distribution of tweet lengths. Extremely short tweets are understandably very rare, but it doesn&#8217;t take long for the distribution to reach its first mode at 35 characters. The curve gradually and smoothly trails off to a local minimum around 116 characters, before positively spiking after 135. The average length is a bit more than 68 characters and the median a bit lower at 62.</p>
